        <tax:p>Remarks.<tax:name obkms_id="741ad00c-4216-4656-a0bc-08fda26447db" obkms_process="TRUE"><tax:xmldata><dwc:Kingdom>Animalia</dwc:Kingdom><dwc:Class>Insecta</dwc:Class><dwc:Order>Hemiptera</dwc:Order><dwc:Family>Cixiidae</dwc:Family><dwc:Genus>Oecleopsis</dwc:Genus><dwc:Species>sinicus</dwc:Species><dwc:taxonRank>species</dwc:taxonRank></tax:xmldata>Oecleopsis sinicus</tax:name> closely resembles<tax:name obkms_id="3b522590-0f3d-4ee5-a69e-ac39d3199bf4" obkms_process="TRUE"><tax:xmldata><dwc:Kingdom>Animalia</dwc:Kingdom><dwc:Class>Insecta</dwc:Class><dwc:Order>Hemiptera</dwc:Order><dwc:Family>Cixiidae</dwc:Family><dwc:Genus>Oecleopsis</dwc:Genus><dwc:Species>bifidus</dwc:Species><dwc:taxonRank>species</dwc:taxonRank></tax:xmldata>O. bifidus</tax:name>,<tax:name obkms_id="f5458de1-2bc2-4d6e-8a9a-2ebb03aff954" obkms_process="TRUE"><tax:xmldata><dwc:Kingdom>Animalia</dwc:Kingdom><dwc:Class>Insecta</dwc:Class><dwc:Order>Hemiptera</dwc:Order><dwc:Family>Cixiidae</dwc:Family><dwc:Genus>Oecleopsis</dwc:Genus><dwc:Species>mori</dwc:Species><dwc:taxonRank>species</dwc:taxonRank></tax:xmldata>O. mori</tax:name>,<tax:name obkms_id="8eb56ce8-cc9d-44a1-9617-ef0de7d503d0" obkms_process="TRUE"><tax:xmldata><dwc:Kingdom>Animalia</dwc:Kingdom><dwc:Class>Insecta</dwc:Class><dwc:Order>Hemiptera</dwc:Order><dwc:Family>Cixiidae</dwc:Family><dwc:Genus>Oecleopsis</dwc:Genus><dwc:Species>artemisiae</dwc:Species><dwc:taxonRank>species</dwc:taxonRank></tax:xmldata>O. artemisiae</tax:name> and<tax:name obkms_id="41119adf-988d-4066-b9f4-41054aff07c2" obkms_process="TRUE"><tax:xmldata><dwc:Kingdom>Animalia</dwc:Kingdom><dwc:Class>Insecta</dwc:Class><dwc:Order>Hemiptera</dwc:Order><dwc:Family>Cixiidae</dwc:Family><dwc:Genus>Oecleopsis</dwc:Genus><dwc:Species>wuyiensis</dwc:Species><dwc:taxonRank>species</dwc:taxonRank></tax:xmldata>O. wuyiensis</tax:name> sp. nov. in the presence of a bifurcate apex of the flagellum. It differs from<tax:name obkms_id="56194687-4517-4516-843b-e83998cd8204" obkms_process="TRUE"><tax:xmldata><dwc:Kingdom>Animalia</dwc:Kingdom><dwc:Class>Insecta</dwc:Class><dwc:Order>Hemiptera</dwc:Order><dwc:Family>Cixiidae</dwc:Family><dwc:Genus>Oecleopsis</dwc:Genus><dwc:Species>bifidus</dwc:Species><dwc:taxonRank>species</dwc:taxonRank></tax:xmldata>O. bifidus</tax:name> in the presence of two subapical spines instead of one on the flagellum, from<tax:name obkms_id="21720a2a-686e-4d2d-9e00-7a9cfec193d5" obkms_process="TRUE"><tax:xmldata><dwc:Kingdom>Animalia</dwc:Kingdom><dwc:Class>Insecta</dwc:Class><dwc:Order>Hemiptera</dwc:Order><dwc:Family>Cixiidae</dwc:Family><dwc:Genus>Oecleopsis</dwc:Genus><dwc:Species>mori</dwc:Species><dwc:taxonRank>species</dwc:taxonRank></tax:xmldata>O.mori</tax:name> in the insertion of the apical spine on the right side of the periandrium which is inserted closer to the apex of the aedeagus in<tax:name obkms_id="0fe1d847-4fc7-4da3-ac81-4358d3908bca" obkms_process="TRUE"><tax:xmldata><dwc:Kingdom>Animalia</dwc:Kingdom><dwc:Class>Insecta</dwc:Class><dwc:Order>Hemiptera</dwc:Order><dwc:Family>Cixiidae</dwc:Family><dwc:Genus>Oecleopsis</dwc:Genus><dwc:Species>sinicus</dwc:Species><dwc:taxonRank>species</dwc:taxonRank></tax:xmldata>O.sinicus</tax:name>, and in the rami of bifurcation which are extremely asymmetrical in<tax:name obkms_id="61e0c8fe-b175-44e0-a48a-632f52be5943" obkms_process="TRUE"><tax:xmldata><dwc:Kingdom>Animalia</dwc:Kingdom><dwc:Class>Insecta</dwc:Class><dwc:Order>Hemiptera</dwc:Order><dwc:Family>Cixiidae</dwc:Family><dwc:Genus>Oecleopsis</dwc:Genus><dwc:Species>mori</dwc:Species><dwc:taxonRank>species</dwc:taxonRank></tax:xmldata>O.mori</tax:name>, from<tax:name obkms_id="1e7968bf-4a22-4c0e-952c-134d799ca202" obkms_process="TRUE"><tax:xmldata><dwc:Kingdom>Animalia</dwc:Kingdom><dwc:Class>Insecta</dwc:Class><dwc:Order>Hemiptera</dwc:Order><dwc:Family>Cixiidae</dwc:Family><dwc:Genus>Oecleopsis</dwc:Genus><dwc:Species>artemisiae</dwc:Species><dwc:taxonRank>species</dwc:taxonRank></tax:xmldata>O. artemisiae</tax:name> in the apical spine on the right side of the periandrium which is much longer in<tax:name obkms_id="d74380f8-fd04-47e9-a271-447cff1ae61d" obkms_process="TRUE"><tax:xmldata><dwc:Kingdom>Animalia</dwc:Kingdom><dwc:Class>Insecta</dwc:Class><dwc:Order>Hemiptera</dwc:Order><dwc:Family>Cixiidae</dwc:Family><dwc:Genus>Oecleopsis</dwc:Genus><dwc:Species>artemisiae</dwc:Species><dwc:taxonRank>species</dwc:taxonRank></tax:xmldata>O. artemisiae</tax:name>, and from<tax:name obkms_id="ad5f4136-b904-4a47-8f89-948373fface4" obkms_process="TRUE"><tax:xmldata><dwc:Kingdom>Animalia</dwc:Kingdom><dwc:Class>Insecta</dwc:Class><dwc:Order>Hemiptera</dwc:Order><dwc:Family>Cixiidae</dwc:Family><dwc:Genus>Oecleopsis</dwc:Genus><dwc:Species>wuyiensis</dwc:Species><dwc:taxonRank>species</dwc:taxonRank></tax:xmldata>O. wuyiensis</tax:name> sp. nov. in the symmetrical rami of bifurcation (asymmetrical in<tax:name obkms_id="7be2f53b-ecdc-46ca-b0bc-c23d6f54b1c7" obkms_process="TRUE"><tax:xmldata><dwc:Kingdom>Animalia</dwc:Kingdom><dwc:Class>Insecta</dwc:Class><dwc:Order>Hemiptera</dwc:Order><dwc:Family>Cixiidae</dwc:Family><dwc:Genus>Oecleopsis</dwc:Genus><dwc:Species>wuyiensis</dwc:Species><dwc:taxonRank>species</dwc:taxonRank></tax:xmldata>O. wuyiensis</tax:name> sp. nov.). In<tax:name obkms_id="6ae8099c-864c-450f-a4f6-c6c5f6251a31" obkms_process="TRUE"><tax:xmldata><dwc:Kingdom>Animalia</dwc:Kingdom><dwc:Class>Insecta</dwc:Class><dwc:Order>Hemiptera</dwc:Order><dwc:Family>Cixiidae</dwc:Family><dwc:Genus>Oecleopsis</dwc:Genus><dwc:Species>sinicus</dwc:Species><dwc:taxonRank>species</dwc:taxonRank></tax:xmldata>O. sinicus</tax:name>, the dorsal subapical spine is larger, tapering to the end, directed left-cephalad, the ventral one smaller, arising from the base of the apical process, the basal portion directed left-cephalad and the apex curved ventrad.</tax:p>
